title.narrative: OUTPUT 2.1: PRE-SCHOOL LEARNING

description.narrative: By 2020, 7,200 children aged 3-5 years in the 5 target districts, especially in remote areas, benefit from quality early learning programmes., which contributes to Early Childhood Development, Early Learning, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Learning And Child-Friendly Schools, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, children, especially the most disadvantaged children, benefit from inclusive, quality early learning and basic education with improved learning outcomes attained.

description.narrative: Community Based Preschool (CBPS) Programme continued to focus on developing a model that can be scaled up nation-wide to expand access by complementing existing preschool services while ensuring that the quality of learning met the required standards. The enrolment in UNICEF supported CBPS contributes roughly 3- 4 percent of total preschool enrolment in the country. Community engagement has been strengthened through the development of CBPS Management guidelines and training for School Management Committees helped strengthen local capacity to manage CBPS. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:03/02/2021
